! Macro & variable calls

* Simple variable: <<now>>
* Variable with no params: <<currentTiddler>>
* Positional params: <<myMacro "first" "second">>
* Positional with single quotes: <<myMacro 'first' 'second'>>
* Triple-quoted param: <<myMacro """value with "quotes" inside""">>
* Named params (colon): <<myMacro first:"a" second:"b">>
* Named params (equals): <<myMacro param="value" n=5 flag=yes>>
* Mixed named/positional: <<myMacro "pos" named:"val">>
* Dynamic params: <<myMacro ref={{SomeTiddler}} sub={{{ [tag[x]] }}}>>

(The `<<__param__>>` substituted-parameter form is only valid inside a `\define`
macro body — see the //Pragmas// demo.)

!! Multi-valued variables

Display form: ((myListVariable)) and with a separator ((myListVariable||, )).

!! Widgets

<$link to="HelloThere">A link widget</$link>

<$text text="Some plain text via a widget"/>

<$list filter="[tag[done]sort[title]]" variable="item">
* <<item>>
</$list>

<$list filter="[tag[done]]" emptyMessage="Nothing here">

! Block-mode content (blank line after opening tag)

* <<currentTiddler>>
</$list>

<$let currentColour="red" size="big">
Inside a let widget: <<currentColour>> / <<size>>.
</$let>

<$set name="myVar" value="hello">
<<myVar>>
</$set>

<$wikify name="rendered" text="<<now>>">
Rendered: <<rendered>>
</$wikify>

!! Self-closing and nested widgets

<$transclude tiddler="SomeTiddler" mode="block"/>

<$list filter="[tag[done]]">
<$link to=<<currentTiddler>>><$view field="title"/></$link>
</$list>

!! Attribute value forms

<$mywidget
	plain=unquoted
	quoted="double"
	single='single'
	number=42
	boolean=yes
	macro=<<now>>
	dynamicparam=<<myMacro p={{Ref}}>>
	transclude={{SomeTiddler}}
	field={{SomeTiddler!!title}}
	index={{SomeData##key}}
	filtered={{{ [tag[x]] }}}
	mvv=((myListVariable))
	substituted=`value is $(currentTiddler)$ and ${ [tag[x]count[]] }$`
	tripleSubstituted=```a literal ` backtick and $(currentTiddler)$```
	filter="[tag[done]] =>doneItems +[!is[draft]]"
/>

!! HTML tags

<div class="outer" style.color="blue" data-foo="bar">
<span class="inner">Plain HTML works too</span>
<br/>
<hr class="sep"/>
</div>

!! Conditionals

<%if [{!!draft.of}] %>
This is a draft.
<%elseif [<currentTiddler>has[modified]] %>
Has a modified date.
<%else%>
Neither.
<%endif%>
